Technically, it is spring, yet it will be a while before all of the wonderful summer fruits and veggies arrive. But let’s not forget about all of the great winter veggies! Sometimes it seems like there aren’t very many options, but this colorful salad will brighten up any winter day. 



![IMG_1372.JPG](/content/IMG_1372-JPG.jpg)

<br>

**Colorful Cabbage Salad:**

*(Serves 4)*

	Ingredients:

* ¼ medium head cabbage

* 4 carrots

* 4 T chopped chives

* 2 T olive oil

* 1 tsp red wine vinegar

* Salt & pepper to taste

<br>

	Directions:

1. Shred cabbage and carrots in a food processor or by hand.

2. Mix the cabbage, carrots, and chives in a serving bowl.

3. Create the dressing: Mix the oil, vinegar, and salt & pepper together before pouring onto salad.

4. Stir, and adjust the salt & pepper if needed. Enjoy!

